HEADWORD: Prosopolepsy
<hw>Pros`o*po*lep"sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>pro`swpon</grk> a face, a person + <?/ a taking, receiving, <?/ to
take.]</ety> <def>Respect of persons; especially, a premature opinion or
prejudice against a person, formed from his external appearance.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
